I’m trying to access our team’s DynamoDB database for an app that pulls data from our tables on DynamoDB and displays it to a html page. The first time I tried seeing if I could pull data, errors showed, saying that I needed to migrate from javascript v2 to v3 and I followed the guide that they provided with the error message. After following the guide, it still gave me the same errors so I decided to completely restart the process with downloading the libraries and everything. So far their javascript v3 setup guide has been extremely confusing and doesn’t provide enough details on what I’m supposed to do for their second prerequisite. Has anyone done anything similar and could help me with this? Thanks

This is the guide I was following

docs.aws.amazon.com

Getting started in Node.js - AWS SDK for JavaScript

Create a simple Node.js app with the SDK for JavaScript.
